README for LibGame
------------------

LibGame is a set of C++ classes useful for creating games.  These classes fall into 
one of several categories:

    - core (initialization, inputs events, timers)
    - graphics (primitives, sprites (BMP), surfaces)
    - audio (WAV)
    - video (future)
    - screens
    - game state
    - threading

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Files within this directory:

    demo/       - source for example game using LibGame (tic tac toe)

    docs/       - generated docs from UML model

    ide/        - IDE project files

    include/    - common include files

    lib/        - common libraries

	model/		- UML model for LibGame

	src/		- source for LibGame library (output tree for generated code)

    reference/  - reference code from DrawSdl "C" library

	Makefile	- makefile to make target 'LibGame' for Unix systems

	README		- this file

	REVISION	- revision history

	common.mk	- common tools stuff

    coverage.sh - code coverage test script

	timing.mk	- build timing stuff

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

To unpack distribution file:

	tar xzvf game-x.x.x.tgz
	
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

To make and install LibGame executables:

	cd game

	<edit common.mk to change compilers if necessary>
	<edit Makefile to change installed directory if desired>
	
	make all

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

To use example game:

//	Usage:	game [-h|-v]|[-l <file>]
//
//	Options:
//		        -h	        - get options help
//
//              -v          - display version
//
//              -l <file>   - load saved game

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Examples:

show help, list usage

    game -h

show version

    game -v

run demo with custom starting pattern

    game -g mygame.save

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

